Use `$md` when a template body should be formatted as Markdown.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    content = [$md:
        # Welcome

        This text becomes **formatted content**.
    ]
]

Small inline code spans use one backtick on each side.

Use `$code("bst")` or another language name for a full highlighted code block.

Beanstalk Markdown is deliberately small. It does not support fenced code
blocks or pipe tables.
